<br/>

<!-- inc publications_db -->

 <strong>March 21,  2016</strong><p><i></i><p><strong>Alumnus Steven Anderson receives 2016 Lauds & Laurels Award
</strong><p><p><P>
UC Irvine honors alumnus Steven Anderson (B.S. &rsquo;86), managing partner at <A HREF="http://www.quinnemanuel.com/attorneys/anderson-steven-m#page=0&byChar=&byProfileType=&bySearch=anderson&byOffice=&byPracticeArea=&byLawCleark=&byFSFP=&byADP=">Quinn Emanuel Urquhart & Sullivan</A> and a distinguished lawyer in the computer science and technology field, with a <A HREF="https://news.uci.edu/alumni/uci-names-18-recipients-of-46th-annual-lauds-laurels-awards/">2016 Lauds and Laurels Award</A>. Anderson is one of this year&rsquo;s 18 recipients of the UCI Alumni Association&rsquo;s highest honor, and this year&rsquo;s only ICS alum.

<P>
Anderson graduated magna cum laude and Phi Beta Kappa with a B.S. in Information and Computer Sciences in 1986. From there, he attended Harvard Law School, graduating cum laude with his J.D. in 1989. He served as editor of the <I>Harvard Journal of Law and Technology</I> from 1987 to 1989. Anderson now practices law in the areas of intellectual property litigation and patent litigation. Over the years, he has provided counsel in a variety of computer and tech-related areas, including microprocessors and microcomputers, ultrasonic toothbrushes, and prepaid wireless telecommunication systems and methods, among many others. His clients have included DIRECTV, Freedom Wireless, Seiko Epson and Motorola Mobility. <I><A HREF="http://www.lamag.com/">Los Angeles Magazine</A></I> has also named Anderson a &ldquo;Super Lawyer&rdquo; several times over.

<P>
Anderson and his fellow awardees will be formally honored at the <A HREF="http://engage.alumni.uci.edu/s/1735/alumni/index1col.aspx?sid=1735&gid=2&pgid=830&cid=1994&ecid=1994&crid=0&calpgid=427&calcid=1085">46th Annual Lauds & Laurels Gala</A>, held May 12 at the new <A HREF="http://www.avirvine.com/">[AV] Irvine</A> venue near the Irvine Spectrum. The Lauds and Laurels Award Ceremony has been a UCI Alumni Association tradition since 1970, making it the university&rsquo;s oldest award ceremony. The annual tradition has recognized more than 750 members of the UC Irvine community for their service to the university, the community or their profession.





<IMG SRC="/bin/img/articles/Lauds_Laurels_2016_Steven_Anderson.jpg" STYLE='width: 100%; margin: 0.5em 0; '>
<br><TITLE>Alumnus Steven Anderson receives 2016 Lauds & Laurels Award
</TITLE>

</div>
</blockquote>
